# Role-lane registry — one lane per line.
#
# Format: <lane-name> [assistant-of:<main-role> | parallel-of:<main-role>]
# - Lines starting with '#' and blank lines are ignored.
# - A main role has no 'assistant-of:' / 'parallel-of:' marker.
# - An assistant lane declares its main role with 'assistant-of:<main-role>'.
#   Assistant lanes carry bounded support-scope authority, not structural authority.
# - A parallel-main lane declares its discipline twin with 'parallel-of:<main-role>'.
#   Parallel-main lanes carry full main-role authority (structural decisions,
#   design reports, skill edits) — they are a second seat at the discipline,
#   not a subordinate lane. New shape as of 2026-05-21; see
#   reports/second-designer/2-persona-orchestrate-lane-management-2026-05-21.md.
#
# This file is a transitional bash-readable format. The destination is
# orchestrate/roles.nota — a typed Nota record read by a Rust-rewritten
# tools/orchestrate. The Rust rewrite is specified in
# reports/second-designer-assistant/2-orchestrate-rust-rewrite-design-2026-05-17.md.

operator
second-operator                   parallel-of:operator
second-operator-assistant         assistant-of:operator
designer
second-designer                   parallel-of:designer
third-designer                    parallel-of:designer
designer-assistant                assistant-of:designer
system-specialist
system-assistant                  assistant-of:system-specialist
second-system-assistant           assistant-of:system-specialist
poet
poet-assistant                    assistant-of:poet
